      "writtenOn": "2018-11-29T22:41:50Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This is a bit scary.  link.Label is unvalidated user input text, and over here we are inserting it directly into the DOM as text.  This opens Milo up to XSS attacks.\n\nThere are a couple of options:\n1. Use a client side templating engine.  It appears vis supports several: http://visjs.org/docs/timeline/#Templates\n2. Render all html on the server side using Go templates, client-side only deals with data.\n3. Keep the javascript as-is, but sanitize all text on the server side.\n\nGenerally I\u0027d prefer #2 but I don\u0027t know how feasible that is.  #1 might be okay if the templating engine is low cost (in terms of perceived user latency), but I have doubts about that.  #3 is probably the practical option, but we just need to be very careful everything is sanitized.",
      "revId": "5ed0a6664e1ccb6a859621e6920b3027e7e01cc3",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
